original: Boström, Johan Henning, kyrkoherde, Lillebyn, f. 7/1/95 i Lane-Her-restad, Gi^gs o. Boh. 1., av sjökapten Johan Boström o. Sara Nilsdotter. G. 21 m. Bengta Lindman. Barn: Mary f. 22, Martha 24, Vera 27, Bengt 30. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 14, teol. kand. i Lund 18, prästv. i Karlstad s. å. Adj. i Brattfors 18-19, kommin. i Gestad 19-39, kyrkoh. i Bolstad sed. 39. Ordf. i Gestads kyrkostämma, barnav:nd o. skolstyr. 19-39, Bolstads kyrkostämma sed. 39, skolstyr. sed. 39, Timmerviks kyrkostift. sed. dess tillkomst, led. av barnav:ndn sed. 39, ordf. sed. 44.
translated: Boström, Johan Henning, clergyman, Lillebyn, b. 7/1/95 in Lane-Her-restad, Gi^gs and Boh. 1., son of sea captain Johan Boström and Sara Nilsdotter. Married on 21/xx to Bengta Lindman. Children: Mary b. 22, Martha b. 24, Vera b. 27, Bengt b. 30. — Completed high school in Gothenburg in 1914, theology degree in Lund in 1918, ordained in Karlstad the same year. Assistant in Brattfors 1918-1919, parish priest in Gestad 1919-1939, and in Bolstad from 1939. Chairman of Gestad's church council, child welfare committee, and school board 1919-1939, Bolstad's church council from 1939, school board from 1939, member of the Timmerviks diocese child welfare committee since its inception, chairman since 1944.
